{
  "texts": [
    "For reference, standard deviations can be computed analytically as follows:",
    "• x is the quantile (the value associated with a given percentile, such as a cutoff score),",
    "• is the mean, • z is the z-score corresponding to a given percentile,",
    "• is the standard deviation.",
    "Thus, by (a) subtracting the cutoff score of a given administration (x) from the mean ; and (b) dividing that by the z-score (z) corresponding to the percentile of the cutoff score (i.e., the percentage of people who did not pass), one is left with the standard deviation ."
  ]
}